  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6570 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6550 (-4.85B) and max positive gamma at 6600 (+1.55B), dealers are in active hedging mode - buying the dip toward 6550 and will sell any push toward 6600. The massive negative GEX concentration from 6550-6570 creates a amplification zone where dealer buying should provide support, but any break below 6550 triggers more mechanical buying in a cascading effect. Key inflection point is 6600 where the gamma profile flips positive and dealer selling pressure kicks in hard.\n\nThe wall break and GEX surge events suggest we're seeing real structural shifts in positioning, with the -88% 5-minute GEX change indicating rapid unwinding of gamma positions that should continue to drive volatile, trending moves.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile bounces between 6550 support and 6600 resistance until one side breaks decisively.",
